---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Commercial EV Charging — Evium Charging"
  description="Turn your commercial property's parking into a competitive advantage. Evium delivers zero-cost, fully managed EV charging infrastructure for office buildings, mixed-use properties, and corporate campuses."
>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       HERO
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="relative min-h-screen flex items-center overflow-hidden bg-evium-dark pt-20">
    <!-- Background grid pattern -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-5" style="background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(45,200,86,0.4) 1px, transparent 1px), linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(45,200,86,0.4) 1px, transparent 1px); background-size: 60px 60px;"></div>

    <!-- Radial glow -->
    <div class="absolute top-1/3 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-[900px] h-[600px] rounded-full opacity-10 pointer-events-none" style="background: radial-gradient(ellipse, #2DC856 0%, transparent 70%);"></div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12 py-24 lg:py-32">
      <div class="max-w-4xl">
        <!-- Eyebrow label -->
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
          <span class="h-px w-10 bg-evium-green"></span>
          <span class="text-evium-green text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase">Commercial Solutions</span>
        </div>

        <h1 class="text-5xl lg:text-7xl font-black leading-[1.05] tracking-tight text-white mb-8">
          Your Building.<br />
          Their Mandate.<br />
          <span class="text-evium-green">Your Advantage.</span>
        </h1>

        <p class="text-xl lg:text-2xl text-white/60 font-medium leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mb-12">
          Corporate tenants now expect EV charging as a baseline amenity. Evium delivers a fully managed, zero-capital charging infrastructure — so your building wins the lease negotiation before the tour begins.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
          <a
            href="/contact/quote"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-3 bg-evium-green text-evium-dark font-bold text-base px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:brightness-110 transition-all duration-200 group"
          >
            Get a Free Site Assessment
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-1" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" />
            </svg>
          </a>
          <a
            href="#shift"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 border border-white/20 text-white/80 font-semibold text-base px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:border-evium-green hover:text-evium-green transition-all duration-200"
          >
            See How It Works
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Stat strip pinned to bottom -->
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 border-t border-white/10 bg-black/20 backdrop-blur-sm">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12 py-6 grid grid-cols-3 gap-6 text-center">
        <div>
          <p class="text-3xl font-black text-evium-green">500+</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-white/50 uppercase tracking-widest mt-1">Chargers Deployed</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-3xl font-black text-evium-green">$0</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-white/50 uppercase tracking-widest mt-1">Upfront Capital</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-3xl font-black text-evium-green">24/7</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-white/50 uppercase tracking-widest mt-1">Managed Support</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       THE COMMERCIAL CHARGING SHIFT
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section id="shift" class="bg-evium-dark-light py-28">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
            <span class="h-px w-10 bg-evium-green"></span>
            <span class="text-evium-green text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase">The Market Shift</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-black text-white leading-tight mb-8">
            EV Charging Is Now a Lease Requirement — Not a Perk
          </h2>
          <p class="text-white/60 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Fortune 500 tenants, law firms, tech companies, and financial institutions have internal sustainability mandates that govern real estate decisions. Charging infrastructure is increasingly a line item in RFPs and lease negotiations — and properties without it are being filtered out before the first showing.
          </p>
          <p class="text-white/60 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-10">
            Buildings that offer managed EV charging signal forward-thinking operations, attract higher-quality tenants, and command stronger lease terms. It's no longer a differentiator — it's table stakes. The question is whether your building is ready.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
            {[
              "Corporate tenants with ESG mandates now require charging in RFP criteria",
              "Properties with charging infrastructure report higher tenant retention",
              "EV adoption among executives and professional staff is accelerating"
            ].map(item => (
              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="mt-1 flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded-full bg-evium-green/15 border border-evium-green/40 flex items-center justify-center">
                  <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-evium-green" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                </span>
                <p class="text-white/70 text-base">{item}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Visual callout card -->
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-evium-dark p-10">
            <div class="absolute -top-px left-10 right-10 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-evium-green/60 to-transparent"></div>
            <p class="text-white/40 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">The Competitive Landscape</p>
            <div class="space-y-6">
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between py-4 border-b border-white/8">
                <span class="text-white/70 font-medium">Buildings with Evium charging</span>
                <span class="text-evium-green font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-wide">Wins RFP</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between py-4 border-b border-white/8">
                <span class="text-white/70 font-medium">Buildings with self-managed charging</span>
                <span class="text-yellow-400/80 font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-wide">Mixed Result</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between py-4">
                <span class="text-white/70 font-medium">Buildings with no EV charging</span>
                <span class="text-red-400/80 font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-wide">Filtered Out</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-8 p-5 rounded-xl bg-evium-green/8 border border-evium-green/20">
              <p class="text-white/80 text-sm leading-relaxed italic">
                "The ROI exceeded our projections. We had three tenants ask about the charging infrastructure during lease renewal discussions."
              </p>
              <p class="text-evium-green text-sm font-semibold mt-3">— Vin Gureeno, Commercial Property, New England</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       PAIN POINTS
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="bg-evium-dark py-28">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="h-px w-10 bg-evium-green"></span>
          <span class="text-evium-green text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase">What Holds Buildings Back</span>
          <span class="h-px w-10 bg-evium-green"></span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-black text-white leading-tight max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Every Concern. Addressed Before You Ask.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {[
          {
            icon: "M12 8c-1.657 0-3 .895-3 2s1.343 2 3 2 3 .895 3 2-1.343 2-3 2m0-8c1.11 0 2.08.402 2.599 1M12 8V7m0 1v8m0 0v1m0-1c-1.11 0-2.08-.402-2.599-1M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z",
            title: "Capital Expenditure",
            body: "Charging infrastructure can run six figures. Evium's no-cost model eliminates upfront spend entirely — hardware, installation, and electrical work are fully covered."
          },
          {
            icon: "M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z",
            title: "Multi-Tenant Complexity",
            body: "Multiple tenants with different needs, billing structures, and access rights. Evium's portal handles tenant group segmentation, custom pricing, and per-group revenue reporting."
          },
          {
            icon: "M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z",
            title: "Electrical Infrastructure",
            body: "Load management, panel capacity, permits — it's complex. Evium handles the full electrical assessment, design, permit pull, and utility coordination."
          },
          {
            icon: "M10.325 4.317c.426-1.756 2.924-1.756 3.35 0a1.724 1.724 0 002.573 1.066c1.543-.94 3.31.826 2.37 2.37a1.724 1.724 0 001.065 2.572c1.756.426 1.756 2.924 0 3.35a1.724 1.724 0 00-1.066 2.573c.94 1.543-.826 3.31-2.37 2.37a1.724 1.724 0 00-2.572 1.065c-.426 1.756-2.924 1.756-3.35 0a1.724 1.724 0 00-2.573-1.066c-1.543.94-3.31-.826-2.37-2.37a1.724 1.724 0 00-1.065-2.572c-1.756-.426-1.756-2.924 0-3.35a1.724 1.724 0 001.066-2.573c-.94-1.543.826-3.31 2.37-2.37.996.608 2.296.07 2.572-1.065z M15 12a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z",
            title: "Ongoing Maintenance",
            body: "Who do you call when a charger goes offline? Evium monitors every unit 24/7 and dispatches service remotely or on-site — property management has nothing to do."
          },
          {
            icon: "M9 12h6m-6 4h6m2 5H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z",
            title: "Revenue & Billing Tracking",
            body: "Charging revenue is distributed across dozens of sessions per day. Evium's portal aggregates all billing, provides transparent revenue reports, and handles driver payment collection."
          },
          {
            icon: "M8 7V3m8 4V3m-9 8h10M5 21h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2z",
            title: "Timeline & Disruption",
            body: "Most commercial deployments complete in weeks, not months. Evium coordinates installation to minimize disruption to tenants and daily operations."
          }
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="group rounded-xl border border-white/8 bg-evium-dark-light p-8 hover:border-evium-green/30 transition-all duration-300">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-evium-green/10 border border-evium-green/20 flex items-center justify-center mb-6 group-hover:bg-evium-green/15 transition-colors duration-300">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-evium-green" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d={item.icon} />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-lg mb-3">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-white/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">{item.body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       WHAT EVIUM DELIVERS — 5-STAGE PROCESS
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="bg-evium-dark-light py-28">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-20 items-start">
        <div class="lg:sticky lg:top-28">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
            <span class="h-px w-10 bg-evium-green"></span>
            <span class="text-evium-green text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase">What We Deliver</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-black text-white leading-tight mb-8">
            Turnkey Means We Handle All of It
          </h2>
          <p class="text-white/60 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-8">
            From the first site walk to year-five maintenance, Evium manages the entire lifecycle. Building management signs off at key milestones — that's it. No contractor coordination, no vendor management, no software configuration.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/contact/quote"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 bg-evium-green text-evium-dark font-bold text-sm px-7 py-3.5 rounded-lg hover:brightness-110 transition-all duration-200 group"
          >
            Start Your Assessment
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-1" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" />
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          {[
            {
              step: "01",
              title: "Site Assessment",
              body: "Evium's team evaluates your parking layout, electrical infrastructure, load capacity, and tenant mix. We model the optimal hardware configuration and identify available utility rebates."
            },
            {
              step: "02",
              title: "Planning & Hardware Selection",
              body: "We specify charger types, quantities, and locations based on your building's needs — mix of L2 wall-mounted units for dedicated tenant parking and pedestal-style for visitor and surface lots."
            },
            {
              step: "03",
              title: "Agreement, Permits & Compliance",
              body: "Evium handles the financial agreement, pulls all required electrical permits, and manages utility interconnection paperwork. You review and sign — we do the rest."
            },
            {
              step: "04",
              title: "Installation & Software Setup",
              body: "Licensed electricians install hardware to code. We configure the OCPP-compliant software portal, set up tenant access groups, pricing rules, and connect payment processing."
            },
            {
              step: "05",
              title: "Ongoing Support & Management",
              body: "24/7 remote monitoring, proactive fault detection, on-site dispatch when needed, and monthly revenue reporting. Your charging infrastructure runs itself."
            }
          ].map(item => (
            <div class="group flex gap-6 p-7 rounded-xl border border-white/8 bg-evium-dark hover:border-evium-green/25 transition-all duration-300">
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 text-evium-green/30 font-black text-4xl leading-none group-hover:text-evium-green/50 transition-colors duration-300">{item.step}</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-lg mb-2">{item.title}</h3>
                <p class="text-white/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">{item.body}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       ACCESS CONTROL & MULTI-TENANT MANAGEMENT
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="bg-evium-dark py-28">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="h-px w-10 bg-evium-green"></span>
          <span class="text-evium-green text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase">Owner Portal</span>
          <span class="h-px w-10 bg-evium-green"></span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-black text-white leading-tight max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          One Building. Many Tenants. Total Control.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-white/55 text-lg mt-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          Commercial properties have complex access needs. Evium's portal gives building managers granular control over every charging session — segmented by tenant, user group, and vehicle type.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-12">
        {[
          {
            title: "Tenant Group Segmentation",
            body: "Create distinct access groups for each tenant company. Set individual pricing tiers, usage limits, and access schedules per group. Employees of Tenant A see different rates than Tenant B's staff.",
            icon: "M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z"
          },
          {
            title: "Visitor & Public Access",
            body: "Define open-access chargers for building visitors with credit card pay-as-you-go. Separate from employee-dedicated units. Manage session time limits to keep stalls turning over.",
            icon: "M15 7a2 2 0 012 2m4 0a6 6 0 01-7.743 5.743L11 17H9v2H7v2H4a1 1 0 01-1-1v-2.586a1 1 0 01.293-.707l5.964-5.964A6 6 0 1121 9z"
          },
          {
            title: "Revenue Reporting by Group",
            body: "Monthly reports break down charging revenue by tenant group, individual user, and time of day. Export data for property accounting. Full audit trail for every session.",
            icon: "M9 19v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2zm0 0V9a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v10m-6 0a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v14a2 2 0 01-2 2h-2a2 2 0 01-2-2z"
          }
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-white/8 bg-evium-dark-light p-8">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-evium-green/10 border border-evium-green/20 flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-evium-green" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d={item.icon} />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-lg mb-3">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-white/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">{item.body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <!-- Portal feature list -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/8 bg-evium-dark-light p-10">
        <p class="text-white/40 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-8">Full Portal Feature Set</p>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
          {[
            "OCPP 1.6+ compliant platform",
            "Custom access codes & RFID",
            "Real-time session monitoring",
            "Remote start / stop / reboot",
            "Driver app for tenants",
            "Automated billing & receipts",
            "Load balancing controls",
            "Peak demand management",
            "API integration available",
            "White-label portal option",
            "Usage analytics dashboard",
            "Fault alert notifications"
          ].map(feature => (
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-evium-green flex-shrink-0"></span>
              <span class="text-white/65 text-sm">{feature}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       HARDWARE FOR COMMERCIAL
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="bg-evium-dark-light py-28">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="h-px w-10 bg-evium-green"></span>
          <span class="text-evium-green text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase">Hardware</span>
          <span class="h-px w-10 bg-evium-green"></span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-black text-white leading-tight max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Purpose-Specified Hardware for Every Parking Environment
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <!-- EVOCHARGE L2 Wall Mount -->
        <div class="group relative rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-evium-dark overflow-hidden hover:border-evium-green/30 transition-all duration-300">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-500" style="background: radial-gradient(ellipse at top, rgba(45,200,86,0.04) 0%, transparent 60%);"></div>
          <div class="p-8 pb-0">
            <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-evium-green/10 border border-evium-green/20 rounded-full px-4 py-1.5 mb-6">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-evium-green"></span>
              <span class="text-evium-green text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider">Dedicated Tenant Parking</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-white font-black text-2xl mb-3">EVOCHARGE L2 Wall-Mount</h3>
            <p class="text-white/55 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Sleek, compact wall-mounted Level 2 chargers ideal for structured parking garages and dedicated tenant stalls. RFID and app access control built in. Networked for real-time monitoring.
            </p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8">
              {[
                ["Output", "7.2 – 11.5 kW"],
                ["Connector", "SAE J1772 / CCS"],
                ["Access", "RFID + App"],
                ["Mounting", "Wall / Pedestal"]
              ].map(([label, value]) => (
                <div class="rounded-lg bg-white/5 p-3">
                  <p class="text-white/40 text-xs uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">{label}</p>
                  <p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm">{value}</p>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-end justify-center h-56 px-8">
            <img
              src="/images/chargers/evocharge/evium-evocharge-l2-wallmount.png"
              alt="EVOCHARGE L2 Wall-Mount Charger"
              class="max-h-full object-contain drop-shadow-2xl transition-transform duration-500 group-hover:scale-105"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Siemens VersiCharge AC -->
        <div class="group relative rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-evium-dark overflow-hidden hover:border-evium-green/30 transition-all duration-300">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-500" style="background: radial-gradient(ellipse at top, rgba(45,200,86,0.04) 0%, transparent 60%);"></div>
          <div class="p-8 pb-0">
            <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-white/5 border border-white/15 rounded-full px-4 py-1.5 mb-6">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-white/40"></span>
              <span class="text-white/60 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider">Visitor &amp; Surface Parking</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-white font-black text-2xl mb-3">Siemens VersiCharge AC</h3>
            <p class="text-white/55 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Robust AC charging units available in wall-mount and pedestal configurations. Ideal for surface lots, visitor areas, and mixed-use zones requiring flexible placement and open or card-controlled access.
            </p>
